Birding with Melissa Kelly on the Lake Cachuma Eagle Count.  Weather: following largest storm of the year. 55F at 8am, 65oF by noon.  No wind.  Coverage: We started from the marina on the pontoon boat which took each of 13 or so groups to their respective observations points for the annual Eagle Count.  Liz Mason, Co. Parks Dept., coordinates this count.   Our area covers the W side of Santa Cruz Bay and the Bay as far as it could be viewed from various points along the W side. Original notes reside at the UCSB Center for Biodiversity and Ecological Restoration Field Note Archive: Cachuma 13 Jan 2001.pdf
